# Feature Module Pattern

Feature-based organization for frontend code with consistent structure and barrel exports.

## Feature Directory Structure

Each feature MUST follow this structure:

```
feature-name/
├── components/                 # Feature-specific components
│   ├── ComponentName/
│   │   ├── ComponentName.tsx
│   │   ├── ComponentName.module.css
│   │   └── index.ts
│   └── index.ts               # Barrel export
├── hooks/                      # Feature-specific hooks
│   ├── useFeatureName.ts
│   ├── useFeatureAction.ts
│   └── index.ts               # Barrel export
├── services/                   # Feature API services
│   ├── feature-name.service.ts
│   └── index.ts               # Barrel export
├── types/                      # Feature type definitions
│   ├── feature-name.types.ts
│   └── index.ts               # Barrel export
└── index.ts                   # Main feature barrel export
```

## Barrel Exports

### Main Feature Export

Each feature's `index.ts` MUST export all sub-modules:

```typescript
// features/auth/index.ts
export * from './components';
export * from './hooks';
export * from './services';
export * from './types';
```

### Sub-module Exports

Each sub-directory MUST have its own barrel export:

```typescript
// features/auth/components/index.ts
export { LoginForm } from './LoginForm';
export { SignupForm } from './SignupForm';
export { SocialAuthButtons } from './SocialAuthButtons';
export { AuthToggle } from './AuthToggle';

// Export types too
export type { LoginFormProps } from './LoginForm';
export type { SignupFormProps } from './SignupForm';
```

```typescript
// features/auth/hooks/index.ts
export { useAuth } from './useAuth';
export { useLogin } from './useLogin';
export { useSignup } from './useSignup';
```

```typescript
// features/auth/services/index.ts
export { authService } from './auth.service';
export type { AuthService } from './auth.service';
```

```typescript
// features/auth/types/index.ts
export type {
  User,
  AuthState,
  LoginCredentials,
  SignupCredentials,
  AuthError
} from './auth.types';
```

## Feature Import Patterns

### CORRECT Imports

```typescript
// Import from feature barrel
import { LoginForm, useAuth, authService, User } from '@/features/auth';

// Import from sub-module barrel
import { LoginForm, SignupForm } from '@/features/auth/components';
import { useAuth, useLogin } from '@/features/auth/hooks';
```

### INCORRECT Imports

```typescript
// DON'T import from individual files
import { LoginForm } from '@/features/auth/components/LoginForm/LoginForm';
import { useAuth } from '@/features/auth/hooks/useAuth';
```

## Service Structure

Each feature service handles API calls for that feature:

```typescript
// features/auth/services/auth.service.ts
import { apiClient } from '@/services/api/client';
import type { User, LoginCredentials, SignupCredentials } from '../types';

class AuthService {
  async login(credentials: LoginCredentials): Promise<User> {
    const response = await apiClient.post('/auth/login', credentials);
    return response.data;
  }
  
  async signup(credentials: SignupCredentials): Promise<User> {
    const response = await apiClient.post('/auth/signup', credentials);
    return response.data;
  }
  
  async logout(): Promise<void> {
    await apiClient.post('/auth/logout');
  }
  
  async getCurrentUser(): Promise<User> {
    const response = await apiClient.get('/auth/me');
    return response.data;
  }
}

export const authService = new AuthService();
export type { AuthService };
```

## Custom Hooks Structure

Feature-specific hooks encapsulate business logic:

```typescript
// features/auth/hooks/useAuth.ts
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { authService } from '../services';
import type { User, AuthError } from '../types';

export const useAuth = () => {
  const [user, setUser] = useState<User | null>(null);
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(true);
  const [error, setError] = useState<AuthError | null>(null);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    loadUser();
  }, []);
  
  const loadUser = async () => {
    try {
      const currentUser = await authService.getCurrentUser();
      setUser(currentUser);
    } catch (err) {
      setError(err as AuthError);
    } finally {
      setIsLoading(false);
    }
  };
  
  const login = async (credentials: LoginCredentials) => {
    setIsLoading(true);
    try {
      const user = await authService.login(credentials);
      setUser(user);
      return user;
    } catch (err) {
      setError(err as AuthError);
      throw err;
    } finally {
      setIsLoading(false);
    }
  };
  
  const logout = async () => {
    await authService.logout();
    setUser(null);
  };
  
  return {
    user,
    isLoading,
    error,
    login,
    logout,
    isAuthenticated: !!user,
  };
};
```

## Type Definitions

Feature types define data structures and interfaces:

```typescript
// features/auth/types/auth.types.ts

export interface User {
  id: string;
  email: string;
  name?: string;
  avatar?: string;
  createdAt: string;
}

export interface LoginCredentials {
  email: string;
  password: string;
}

export interface SignupCredentials {
  email: string;
  password: string;
  name?: string;
}

export interface AuthState {
  user: User | null;
  isAuthenticated: boolean;
  isLoading: boolean;
  error: AuthError | null;
}

export interface AuthError {
  code: string;
  message: string;
  field?: string;
}

export type AuthProvider = 'google' | 'github' | 'twitter';
```

## Feature Components

Components specific to a feature stay within that feature:

```typescript
// features/auth/components/LoginForm/LoginForm.tsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { Button, Input } from '@/components/ui';
import { useLogin } from '../../hooks';
import type { LoginCredentials } from '../../types';
import styles from './LoginForm.module.css';

export interface LoginFormProps {
  onSuccess?: () => void;
  onError?: (error: Error) => void;
}

export const LoginForm: React.FC<LoginFormProps> = ({ onSuccess, onError }) => {
  const { login, isLoading, error } = useLogin();
  const [credentials, setCredentials] = useState<LoginCredentials>({
    email: '',
    password: '',
  });
  
  const handleSubmit = async (e: React.FormEvent) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    try {
      await login(credentials);
      onSuccess?.();
    } catch (err) {
      onError?.(err as Error);
    }
  };
  
  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className={styles.form}>
      <Input
        type="email"
        label="Email"
        value={credentials.email}
        onChange={(e) => setCredentials({ ...credentials, email: e.target.value })}
        error={error?.field === 'email' ? error.message : undefined}
      />
      <Input
        type="password"
        label="Password"
        value={credentials.password}
        onChange={(e) => setCredentials({ ...credentials, password: e.target.value })}
        error={error?.field === 'password' ? error.message : undefined}
      />
      <Button type="submit" isLoading={isLoading}>
        Log In
      </Button>
    </form>
  );
};
```

## Feature Categories

### App Features

Main application features (in `features/` directory):

- `auth/` - Authentication and user management
- `brand-kit/` - Brand kit management
- `campaigns/` - Campaign management
- `canvas/` - Canvas editor
- `dashboard/` - Dashboard
- `onboarding/` - User onboarding
- `payment/` - Payment processing
- `posting/` - Post management
- `settings/` - User settings

### Landing Features

Landing page features (in `features/landing/`):

- `landing-page/` - Home page sections
- `blog/` - Blog components
- `legal/` - Legal page components
- `support/` - Support components
- `waitlist/` - Waitlist components

## Cross-Feature Communication

### Through Context

```typescript
// context/AuthContext.tsx
import { createContext } from 'react';
import { useAuth } from '@/features/auth';

export const AuthContext = createContext<ReturnType<typeof useAuth> | null>(null);

export const AuthProvider: React.FC<{ children: React.ReactNode }> = ({ children }) => {
  const auth = useAuth();
  
  return (
    <AuthContext.Provider value={auth}>
      {children}
    </AuthContext.Provider>
  );
};
```

### Through Shared Services

```typescript
// features/campaigns/hooks/useCampaigns.ts
import { useAuth } from '@/features/auth';  // ✓ OK to import from other features
import { campaignService } from '../services';

export const useCampaigns = () => {
  const { user } = useAuth();
  
  const loadCampaigns = async () => {
    if (!user) return [];
    return await campaignService.list(user.id);
  };
  
  // ...
};
```

## Best Practices

1. **Keep Features Independent**: Minimize dependencies between features
2. **Use Barrel Exports**: Always use index.ts for clean imports
3. **Co-locate Code**: Keep related code within the same feature
4. **Shared Code**: Move truly shared code to `components/`, `hooks/`, or `utils/`
5. **Type Safety**: Define types in the feature's types directory
6. **Single Responsibility**: Each feature handles one domain

## When to Create a New Feature

Create a new feature when:
- It represents a distinct domain or user flow
- It has its own data models and API endpoints
- It can be developed/tested independently
- It has 3+ related components or hooks

DON'T create a feature for:
- Single-use components (put in relevant page directory)
- Utility functions (put in `utils/`)
- Shared UI components (put in `components/ui/`)
- Global state management (put in `context/`)

## Example: Complete Feature

```
features/brand-kit/
├── components/
│   ├── BrandKitForm/
│   │   ├── BrandKitForm.tsx
│   │   ├── BrandKitForm.module.css
│   │   └── index.ts
│   ├── ColorPicker/
│   │   ├── ColorPicker.tsx
│   │   ├── ColorPicker.module.css
│   │   └── index.ts
│   └── index.ts                # export * from './BrandKitForm'; ...
├── hooks/
│   ├── useBrandKit.ts          # CRUD operations
│   ├── useColorScheme.ts       # Color management
│   └── index.ts                # export * from './useBrandKit'; ...
├── services/
│   ├── brand-kit.service.ts    # API calls
│   └── index.ts                # export { brandKitService }
├── types/
│   ├── brand-kit.types.ts      # BrandKit, ColorScheme, etc.
│   └── index.ts                # export * from './brand-kit.types'
└── index.ts                    # export * from './components'; ...
```

Usage in pages:

```typescript
// app/(app)/brand-kit/page.tsx
import { BrandKitForm, useBrandKit } from '@/features/brand-kit';

export default function BrandKitPage() {
  const { brandKit, isLoading, update } = useBrandKit();
  
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Brand Kit</h1>
      <BrandKitForm brandKit={brandKit} onSubmit={update} />
    </div>
  );
}
```
